chinese: So what's your plan,Dean?
english: 所以你的计划是什么, Dean?

chinese: I mean,after your internship?
english: 我的意思是, 在你实习结束后?

chinese: I finish school.
english: 我完成学业.

chinese: After school,I look for a job.
english: 完成学业后, 我寻找一份工作.

chinese: With your qualifications,
english: 以你的资历,

chinese: you won't have much of a problem.
english: 你不会有什么大问题的.

chinese: I wish that were true.
english: 我希望那是真的.

chinese: Lots of qualified people can't get work.
english: 很多有资格的人找不到工作.

chinese: Because businesses can't afford to hire people?
english: 因为企业雇不起人吗?

chinese: That's what they say.
english: 那是他们所说的.

chinese: Especially with benefits.
english: 尤其带上福利.

chinese: So I may not get a job for a long time.
english: 所以我可能不会得到一份工作  很长一段时间里.

chinese: And if I can't get a job,
english: 如果我不能得到一份工作.

chinese: unemployment must be too high.
english: 失业率必定是过高了.

chinese: Of course,I still have to pay off my student loans.
english: 当然, 我仍然必须还清我的学生贷款.

chinese: You have to pay for university yourself?
english: 你必须自己支付大学的费用吗?

chinese: Doesn't the government subsidize you?
english: 政府不给你补贴吗?

chinese: Not much.You're pretty much on your own.
english: 不多. 你大多得靠自己.

chinese: Funny how the newspaper headlines start to affect your life.
english: 多有趣啊 报纸头条开始影响你的生活了.

chinese: Unemployment,inflation....
english: 失业, 通货膨胀...

chinese: Well that's not very cheerful,is it?
english: Well 那不是很令人愉快, 是吗?

chinese: If only the sports pages were better!
english: 要是体育版更好一些该多好!
